# 3. IAM Processes & Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)

## 3.1 Purpose
To ensure repeatability, consistency, and auditability of IAM operations through documented end-to-end processes.

## 3.2 Core IAM Processes

### Identity Lifecycle Management (Joiner–Mover–Leaver)
- Automated provisioning from HRIS to Entra ID and AD  
- Manual exceptions workflow integrated with ServiceNow  
- Deprovisioning with Sentinel monitoring for anomalies  

### Access Requests & Approvals
- Access packages via Entra ID Governance  
- Approvers defined through role/department mapping  
- SLA-based approval monitoring  

### Access Reviews & Recertification
- Quarterly and annual reviews aligned with compliance  
- Automated workflows for remediation  
- Audit exports for GDPR/NIS2  

### Privileged Access Management (If Applicable)
- Scoped to AD, Entra ID, and cloud workloads  
- Temporary elevation workflows  

### Application Onboarding
- Standardized integration checklist  
- Authentication alignment (SSO, MFA, Conditional Access)  

## 3.3 Standard Operating Procedures (Examples)
- SOP-01: Create/Delete User Accounts  
- SOP-02: Access Package Request Processing  
- SOP-03: Identity Governance Review Cycle Execution  
- SOP-04: Break Glass Access Management  
- SOP-05: Audit Log Extraction from Sentinel  

